-- Northrop Grumman gets $200 mln U.S. Air Force contract
-- 
-- Thu Jan 11, 2007 8:33am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/11/businesspro-northropgrumman-deal-dc-idUSWNAS713520070111

 

 (Reuters) - Northrop Grumman Corp. ( NOC.N ) said it has been 
awarded a one-year contract, valued at $200 million, by the 
U.S. Air Force's Oklahoma City Air Logistics Center. 

  According to the deal, the defense contractor is 
implementing a more efficient business process for providing 
maintenance and sustainment support for the nation's fleet of 
B-2 stealth bombers, it said in a statement.  (Reporting by Tenzin Pema in Bangalore)